## Scenario — Troubleshooting User Sign-in Issue

### Objective
Simulate a real-world IT support scenario by troubleshooting a user login failure using Okta System Logs.

---

### Scenario
A user reports a login issue:

“Unable to sign in. I tried my password multiple times and I am sure it’s correct.”

User: faisal.abdi@company.com

---

### Steps

### Step 1 — Navigate to System Logs
Go to:

Reports → System Log

Screenshot:  
![System Log Page](screenshots/system-log-page.png)

---

### Step 2 — Filter Logs
Filter events by:

user.account

Screenshot:  
![Filter Applied](screenshots/filter-applied.png)

---

### Step 3 — Refine Search
Search for:

faisal.abdi@company.com

Review recent login attempts.

Screenshot:  
![Search for User](screenshots/search-for-user.png)

---

### Step 4 — Identify Issue
Expand the most recent event.

Check:
- Event type  
- Outcome  
- Authentication details  

Screenshot:  
![Log Event Details](screenshots/log-event-details.png)

---

### Step 5 — Determine Root Cause

Common causes include:
- Account locked after multiple failed attempts  
- Incorrect password attempts  
- Account not activated  
- Password expired  

**In this lab:**  
User account was locked due to multiple failed login attempts.

---

### Step 6 — Resolve Issue

Go to:  
Directory → People → User  

Perform:
- Unlock account  
- Reset password  

Screenshot:  
![Password Reset Action](screenshots/password-reset-action.png)

---

### Result

Successfully troubleshot and resolved user login issue:

- Identified login activity in system logs  
- Analyzed authentication events  
- Determined root cause  
- Restored user access  

